body:
An assertion in file elab_expr fails on trying to pass a packed array field to an instance.

Example code
```SystemVerilog
package abc_pkg;
typedef struct packed {
    logic a;
    logic b;
    logic c;
} whatever_t;

parameter int ARRAY_W = 4;
typedef struct packed {
    whatever_t [ARRAY_W-1:0]    fields;
} breakcore_t;

endpackage

module abc
    import abc_pkg::*;
(
    input  whatever_t [ARRAY_W-1:0]    fields
);

endmodule

module test
    import abc_pkg::*;
();

breakcore_t some_internal;
abc instance_unit (
    .fields(some_internal.fields)
);

endmodule
```

And the output is, when running `iverilog -Wall -gspecify -g2012 *.sv`:
```
*.sv:34: assert: elab_expr.cc:2588: failed assertion !member_comp.index.empty()
```

I've tested this on the 12.0 release, and on the current master (commit hash: `f82c6c7b3ada873015348f728aa3087cdb6661a6`), and got same errors.

